## -- Parsers

FeatureDef:
  @QName: DOMLS|ParseString
  @FeatureVerDef:
    @@QName: DOMLS|ParseString10
    @@f:requires: DOMXML|XMLVersionFeature10
    @@f:version: 1.0
    @@f:instanceOf: DOMLS|ParseString
    @@enDesc:
      A parser class that support the <Feature::DOMLS|ParserString>
      feature version <FeatureVer::1.0> <kwd:MUST> provide a method
      whose name is <DOM::parse>.  The method has at least one 
      parameter whose type is <IF::DOMLS|LSInput||ManakaiDOM|ManakaiDOMLatest>
      or its subset that at least has <A::DOMLS|LSInput||
      ManakaiDOM|ManakaiDOM3.stringData> and <A::DOMLS|LSInput||
      ManakaiDOM|ManakaiDOM3.baseURI> attributes.  The method
      <kwd:MUST> be able to parse an XML document entity
      in the <A::DOMLS|LSInput||ManakaiDOM|ManakaiDOM3.stringData>
      attribute.  Although the parser does not have to
      support full XML 1.0 entities, it <kwd:MUST> support a
      reasonal subset of it.  Applications can request how much level
      the parser supports the parsing of XML by specifying other features
      when they obtains a parser. The method passes the parsed
      document as a <IF::DOMCore|Document||ManakaiDOM|ManakaiDOM>
      object by the way as the <M::DOMLS|LSParser
      ||ManakaiDOM|ManakaiDOM3.parse> method would do.

